  <mainDescription>Business Architecture is a subset of Enterprise Architecture, focusing upon the organization of significant elements of the&#xD;
enterprise and their collaboration to realize the services and business processes supporting the enterprise vision and&#xD;
strategies. Business Architecture is decomposed into Business Domains comprised of Business Functions. Business Functions&#xD;
collaborate to realize business processes and offer services via well-defined interfaces.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br />&#xD;
An enterprise's Business Architecture is driven by its vision, &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../../core.bus.common.extend-ibm/guidances/concepts/business_goal_FDAF5499.html&quot; guid=&quot;_lepv0EcYEd6GBq2DuQ5crg&quot;>goals&lt;/a> and strategies, and influenced by the enterprise's architectural principles.&#xD;
&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br />&#xD;
The Business Architecture is captured in Business Models. Stakeholder perspectives of the Business Architecture are exposed&#xD;
via views into the Business Models. &lt;br /></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription>
